# env.example — rename to .env.example (harness permission rules deny agents
# writing any `.env*` path, so this template ships undotted; a human should run:
#   mv env.example .env.example
# ). Copy to .env for local overrides.
#
# No variables are REQUIRED today: the site is fully static (Astro
# `output: "static"`) and reads no env vars at build or runtime. Entries below
# are documented placeholders for future wiring.

# Canonical site URL (future: Astro `site` config for sitemap/canonical tags).
# PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://example.com

# Real-estate data layer (future: swap the in-memory PLACEHOLDER fixture in
# src/lib/data/properties.ts for a real API/DB).
# PROPERTIES_API_URL=
# PROPERTIES_API_KEY=

# Vercel Web Analytics is auto-injected on Vercel deployments; no key needed.
